race.comment: CARRY ON LIZZY (9) was runner-up first-up at Cootamundra then faded into fourth on the Riverside. Strips fitter and gets weight relief. Can bounce back third-up. LOST YA SOCK (5) was too sharp last start, well and truly having the better of CARRY ON LIZZY in a strong maiden win. Not much tougher here and just needs to repeat the dose but has lacked consistency. HOT ONE (4) has been chasing well and now gets McDougall. Can give this a shake. FREUD (2) comes off a city run where he finished fifth over 1800m at Sandown-Hillside. Drops in trip after a 30-day freshen and debuts for the new stable. Worth some thought.
